# WorldTrading AI Bridge Instructions

Use the shared AI Bridge when work should continue cleanly between Claude Code and Codex.

Before bridge-aware work:
- Read `.ai-bridge/shared/current.md` if it exists.
- For substantial coding, architecture, review, trading-risk, paper/live gate, or deployment tasks, run:
  `py -3.10 tools\ai-bridge.py advise "<task>"`
- Treat `.ai-bridge/runs/<timestamp>/decision.md` as the cross-agent handoff.

Default routing:
- Claude Sonnet is the only default writer for implementation rounds.
- Claude Opus and GPT-5.5 are advisors/reviewers and must stay read-only.
- Use `gpt-5.4-mini` for read-only scan, test triage, and summarization.

Continuity:
- Add durable handoff notes with `py -3.10 tools\ai-bridge.py sync "<note>"`.
- Check shared state with `py -3.10 tools\ai-bridge.py status`.
- Do not store secrets in `.ai-bridge/`.
